---
import ServiceLayout from '@/layouts/ServiceLayout.astro';
import Container from '@/components/ui/Container.astro';
import SchemaFAQ from '@/components/seo/SchemaFAQ.astro';
---

<ServiceLayout
  title="Countertop Installation"
  metaTitle="Countertop Installation Seattle WA | Quartz, Granite & Marble | Best KB Remodeling"
  metaDescription="Professional countertop installation in Seattle. Quartz, granite, marble, and butcher block surfaces expertly measured, fabricated, and installed. Free in-home estimates!"
  slug="countertop-installation"
  category="kitchen"
  heroImage="/images/service-countertop-installation.jpg"
  features={[
    'Precision laser-templating for perfect fit',
    'Professional fabrication with CNC technology',
    'Sink cutout and undermount sink installation',
    'Seam placement optimization for minimal visibility',
    'Edge profile selection (ogee, beveled, waterfall, etc.)',
    'Backsplash coordination and installation',
    'Plumbing reconnection and final sealing',
  ]}
>
  <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">
    <p class="text-xl text-muted leading-relaxed mb-8">
      Countertops define the character of your kitchen or bathroom. They're the surface you interact with most, the centerpiece that ties the room's design together, and the workhorse that withstands daily use for decades. At Best KB Remodeling, we guide Seattle homeowners through every step of the countertop journey — from material selection and laser templating to expert fabrication and flawless installation.
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-[family-name:var(--font-heading)] text-dark-text mt-12 mb-4">
      Our Countertop Installation Process
    </h2>
    <p>
      The journey begins at our design studio or during an in-home consultation where you explore full-size slab samples and choose your material. Once cabinets are in place (or existing cabinets are prepped), our fabrication partner visits your home with laser templating equipment to capture exact measurements down to 1/64 of an inch. This digital template feeds directly into CNC machinery that cuts your countertops with precision impossible to achieve by hand.
    </p>
    <p>
      Fabrication takes approximately 5-10 business days, depending on the material. On installation day, our team carefully delivers, places, and levels each piece, applies color-matched adhesive at seams, cuts and polishes sink openings, and reconnects plumbing. Most installations are completed in a single day. We finish by sealing natural stone surfaces and walking you through care and maintenance instructions.
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-[family-name:var(--font-heading)] text-dark-text mt-12 mb-4">
      Material Options
    </h2>
    <p>
      <strong>Engineered Quartz:</strong> The most popular choice among our Seattle clients, quartz combines ground natural stone with resin binders to create a non-porous, maintenance-free surface that resists stains, scratches, and bacteria. We carry lines from Caesarstone, Cambria, Silestone, and MSI with hundreds of colors and patterns, including options that closely replicate the veining of Calacatta marble without the maintenance concerns.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Natural Granite:</strong> Each granite slab is a one-of-a-kind work of nature. Extremely hard and heat-resistant, granite requires annual sealing but rewards homeowners with unmatched depth and character. We hand-select slabs at local stone yards, so you see and approve your exact slab before fabrication.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Marble:</strong> Prized for its luminous beauty and classic elegance, marble is ideal for bathroom vanities and lower-traffic kitchen areas. We educate every client about marble's maintenance requirements — it does etch and stain more readily than quartz or granite — so you can make an informed decision.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Butcher Block and Specialty Surfaces:</strong> Warm and inviting, solid wood countertops in walnut, maple, or white oak add organic warmth to any kitchen. We also install ultra-compact surfaces like Dekton and Neolith for homeowners seeking extreme durability, as well as recycled glass composite and concrete countertops for a truly unique look.
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-[family-name:var(--font-heading)] text-dark-text mt-12 mb-4">
      Edge Profiles and Design Details
    </h2>
    <p>
      The edge profile of your countertop contributes significantly to the overall aesthetic. We offer a full range of options: clean eased edges for a modern look, classic ogee and bullnose profiles for traditional kitchens, dramatic waterfall edges that cascade down the cabinet sides, and mitered edges that create the illusion of a thick slab. Our design team helps you select the profile that best complements your cabinet style and room design.
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-[family-name:var(--font-heading)] text-dark-text mt-12 mb-4">
      Why Seattle Homeowners Trust Our Countertop Work
    </h2>
    <p>
      Countertop installation demands precision — there's no room for error when working with heavy, expensive stone slabs. Our fabrication partners operate state-of-the-art CNC facilities in the greater Seattle area, ensuring short lead times and exceptional quality control. We've installed countertops in hundreds of kitchens and bathrooms across Seattle, Bellevue, Kirkland, and beyond, building a reputation for impeccable fit and finish.
    </p>
    <p>
      Every installation includes careful protection of your floors, cabinets, and appliances during the process. We clean up thoroughly and dispose of all packaging and old countertop materials. Our 5-year workmanship warranty covers any installation-related issues, and most material manufacturers provide additional warranties ranging from 10 years to lifetime.
    </p>
  </div>

  <!-- Cost Guide CTA -->
  <div class="bg-accent/5 border border-accent/20 rounded-2xl p-8 my-12">
    <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">How Much Does Countertop Installation Cost?</h3>
    <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">Get detailed pricing breakdowns, budget tiers, and money-saving tips in our comprehensive cost guide.</p>
    <a href="/cost-guides/countertop-installation-cost/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 bg-accent text-white px-6 py-3 rounded-lg font-semibold hover:bg-accent-hover transition-colors">View Countertop Installation Cost Guide →</a>
  </div>

  <!-- FAQ Section -->
  <Fragment slot="faq">
    <section class="py-16 lg:py-24 bg-white">
      <Container>
        <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto" data-reveal>
          <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-[family-name:var(--font-heading)] text-dark-text mb-10 text-center">
            Countertop Installation FAQs
          </h2>
          <div class="space-y-4">
            <details class="group bg-light rounded-xl border border-border">
              <summary class="flex items-center justify-between cursor-pointer p-6 font-semibold text-dark-text font-[family-name:var(--font-heading)] text-lg">
                How much do new countertops cost in Seattle?
                <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="w-5 h-5 text-muted transition-transform group-open:rotate-180" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2">
                  <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" />
                </svg>
              </summary>
              <div class="px-6 pb-6 text-muted leading-relaxed">
                Countertop costs vary widely based on material and square footage. Engineered quartz typically runs $55-$120 per square foot installed, granite $50-$100, and marble $60-$150. Butcher block is generally $40-$80 per square foot. A typical Seattle kitchen with 40-50 square feet of countertop space will run $2,500-$6,000 for most materials.
              </div>
            </details>
            <details class="group bg-light rounded-xl border border-border">
              <summary class="flex items-center justify-between cursor-pointer p-6 font-semibold text-dark-text font-[family-name:var(--font-heading)] text-lg">
                Quartz vs. granite: which should I choose?
                <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="w-5 h-5 text-muted transition-transform group-open:rotate-180" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2">
                  <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" />
                </svg>
              </summary>
              <div class="px-6 pb-6 text-muted leading-relaxed">
                Quartz is the better choice if you want zero maintenance, consistent color patterns, and stain resistance. Granite is ideal if you love natural stone's unique variations and don't mind annual sealing. Both are durable and long-lasting. We recommend visiting our showroom to compare samples side by side — most clients can feel the difference immediately.
              </div>
            </details>
            <details class="group bg-light rounded-xl border border-border">
              <summary class="flex items-center justify-between cursor-pointer p-6 font-semibold text-dark-text font-[family-name:var(--font-heading)] text-lg">
                How long does countertop installation take?
                <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="w-5 h-5 text-muted transition-transform group-open:rotate-180" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2">
                  <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" />
                </svg>
              </summary>
              <div class="px-6 pb-6 text-muted leading-relaxed">
                The installation itself typically takes just one day. The full process from template to installation is about 2-3 weeks: laser templating (1 day), fabrication (5-10 business days), and installation (1 day). We coordinate with your plumber to disconnect and reconnect the sink and faucet on installation day.
              </div>
            </details>
            <details class="group bg-light rounded-xl border border-border">
              <summary class="flex items-center justify-between cursor-pointer p-6 font-semibold text-dark-text font-[family-name:var(--font-heading)] text-lg">
                Can you install countertops without replacing cabinets?
                <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="w-5 h-5 text-muted transition-transform group-open:rotate-180" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2">
                  <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" />
                </svg>
              </summary>
              <div class="px-6 pb-6 text-muted leading-relaxed">
                Absolutely — in fact, that's one of our most common projects. As long as your existing cabinets are structurally sound and level, we can remove the old countertops and install new ones directly on top. This pairs beautifully with <a href="/services/cabinet-refacing/" class="text-accent hover:underline">cabinet refacing</a> for a complete kitchen makeover at a fraction of a full remodel's cost.
              </div>
            </details>
            <details class="group bg-light rounded-xl border border-border">
              <summary class="flex items-center justify-between cursor-pointer p-6 font-semibold text-dark-text font-[family-name:var(--font-heading)] text-lg">
                Do quartz countertops stain or chip easily?
                <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="w-5 h-5 text-muted transition-transform group-open:rotate-180" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2">
                  <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" />
                </svg>
              </summary>
              <div class="px-6 pb-6 text-muted leading-relaxed">
                Quartz is highly resistant to both staining and chipping. Its non-porous surface repels liquids like wine, coffee, and cooking oil. While extremely durable, it can chip if struck hard with a heavy object on the edge. Avoid placing extremely hot pots directly on the surface — use trivets to prevent thermal shock. With reasonable care, quartz countertops last a lifetime.
              </div>
            </details>
          </div>
        </div>
      </Container>
    </section>
  </Fragment>

  <SchemaFAQ items={[
    { question: 'How much do new countertops cost in Seattle?', answer: 'Countertop costs vary widely based on material and square footage. Engineered quartz typically runs $55-$120 per square foot installed, granite $50-$100, and marble $60-$150. Butcher block is generally $40-$80 per square foot. A typical Seattle kitchen with 40-50 square feet of countertop space will run $2,500-$6,000 for most materials.' },
    { question: 'Quartz vs. granite: which should I choose?', answer: 'Quartz is the better choice if you want zero maintenance, consistent color patterns, and stain resistance. Granite is ideal if you love natural stone\'s unique variations and don\'t mind annual sealing. Both are durable and long-lasting. We recommend visiting our showroom to compare samples side by side — most clients can feel the difference immediately.' },
    { question: 'How long does countertop installation take?', answer: 'The installation itself typically takes just one day. The full process from template to installation is about 2-3 weeks: laser templating (1 day), fabrication (5-10 business days), and installation (1 day). We coordinate with your plumber to disconnect and reconnect the sink and faucet on installation day.' },
    { question: 'Can you install countertops without replacing cabinets?', answer: 'Absolutely — in fact, that\'s one of our most common projects. As long as your existing cabinets are structurally sound and level, we can remove the old countertops and install new ones directly on top. This pairs beautifully with cabinet refacing for a complete kitchen makeover at a fraction of a full remodel\'s cost.' },
